International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 11 Feb 2022
Source: International Society for Infectious Diseases (ISID)
https://exchange.isid.org/isid/#!*menu=16*browseby=9*sortby=1*trend=19498


The International Society for Infectious Diseases (ISID) would like to welcome the ProMED community to its new online learning platform the Knowledge Exchange and invites you to join its upcoming open-access webinars:

Global dengue outbreak preparedness
-----------------------------------
Date: 15 Feb 2022 at 5:00 AM EST/10:00 AM GMT/11:00 AM CET
Chair: Professor Athanase Badolo (Burkina Faso) and Dr Veasna Duong (Cambodia)
Presentations by: Associate Professor Rachel Lowe (UK), Professor Cameron Simmons (Australia), and Professor Lucy Lum (Malaysia)

HIV - hot topics 2022
---------------------
Date: 8 Mar 2022 at 5:00 AM EST/10:00 AM GMT/11:00 AM CET
Chair: Professor Adeeba Kamarulzaman (Malaysia)
Co-Chair: Dr Seif Al-Abri (Oman)
Speakers: Associate Professor Iskandar Shah Raja Azwa (Malaysia), Professor Jennifer Hoy (Australia), and Dr Rayner Tan (Singapore)

To explore the Knowledge Exchange platform and to register for the upcoming webinars, please click here https://exchange.isid.org/isid/#!*menu=16*browseby=9*sortby=1*trend=19498

The Knowledge Exchange is an online resource that shares open-access educational modules, webinars, podcasts, and interactive discussions. It focuses on sharing evidence-based information for infectious disease management, control and prevention in resource-limited settings. By making these educational resources available to a broad range of healthcare professionals and by offering CME certification, ISID continues to support the prevention, investigation, and management of infectious disease outbreaks.

To sign up for our Knowledge Exchange mailing list and receive information about upcoming events, please click here https://isid.org/joinikeep/.

We hope you find this free resource useful and informative and we encourage you to share the Knowledge Exchange with your networks.

--
Julia Maxwell
director of disease surveillance, ISID
<julia.maxwell@isid.org>

